{{wikipedia}}
==English==

===Noun===
'''lime'''

#the [[green]] [[fruit]] of a lime [[tree]].
#any of the trees that bear limes.
#a white substance (calcium oxide) obtained from [[limestone]].
#:'''Quotations'''
#:*'''1952''': Lime, which is the product of the burning of chalk or limestone, might be bought ready burnt, or it could be burnt in kilns specially constructed in the neighbourhood of the building operations. &mdash; L.F. Salzman, ''Building in England'', p. 149.
#a dry white powder (calcium hydroxide).
#(colour) a light, somewhat yellowish, green [[color|colour]], the colour of the fruit of a lime tree.
#:<table><tr><td>lime colour: &nbsp;</td><td bgcolor="#00FF00" width="80">&nbsp; </td></tr></table>
#the [[linden]] tree.

